36/* Functions which are used by both single and triple DES enctypes */
37
38#include "krb5_locl.h"
39
40/*
41 * A = A xor B. A & B are 8 bytes.
42 */
43
44KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION void KRB5_LIB_CALL
45_krb5_xor8(unsigned char *a, const unsigned char *b)
46{
47 a[0] ^= b[0];
48 a[1] ^= b[1];
49 a[2] ^= b[2];
50 a[3] ^= b[3];
51 a[4] ^= b[4];
52 a[5] ^= b[5];
53 a[6] ^= b[6];
54 a[7] ^= b[7];
55}
56
57#if defined(DES3_OLD_ENCTYPE) || defined(HEIM_WEAK_CRYPTO)
58KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
59_krb5_des_checksum(krb5_context context,
60 const EVP_MD *evp_md,
61 struct _krb5_key_data *key,
62 const void *data,
63 size_t len,
64 Checksum *cksum)
65{
66 struct _krb5_evp_schedule *ctx = key->schedule->data;
67 EVP_MD_CTX *m;
68 DES_cblock ivec;
69 unsigned char *p = cksum->checksum.data;
70
71 krb5_generate_random_block(p, 8);
72
73 m = EVP_MD_CTX_create();
74 if (m == NULL)
75 return krb5_enomem(context);
76
77 EVP_DigestInit_ex(m, evp_md, NULL);
78 EVP_DigestUpdate(m, p, 8);
79 EVP_DigestUpdate(m, data, len);
80 EVP_DigestFinal_ex (m, p + 8, NULL);
81 EVP_MD_CTX_destroy(m);
82 memset (&ivec, 0, sizeof(ivec));
83
84#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x10100000UL
85 ctx->ectx = malloc(sizeof(*ctx->ectx));
86 EVP_CIPHER_CTX_init(ctx->ectx);
87#else
88 ctx->ectx = EVP_CIPHER_CTX_new();
89#endif
90
91 EVP_CipherInit_ex(ctx->ectx, NULL, NULL, NULL, (void *)&ivec, -1);
92 EVP_Cipher(ctx->ectx, p, p, 24);
93
94 return 0;
95}
96
97KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
98_krb5_des_verify(krb5_context context,
99 const EVP_MD *evp_md,
100 struct _krb5_key_data *key,
101 const void *data,
102 size_t len,
103 Checksum *C)
104{
105 struct _krb5_evp_schedule *ctx = key->schedule->data;
106 EVP_MD_CTX *m;
107 unsigned char tmp[24];
108 unsigned char res[16];
109 DES_cblock ivec;
110 krb5_error_code ret = 0;
111
112 m = EVP_MD_CTX_create();
113 if (m == NULL)
114 return krb5_enomem(context);
115
116 memset(&ivec, 0, sizeof(ivec));
117#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x10100000UL
118 ctx->dctx = malloc(sizeof(*ctx->dctx));
119 EVP_CIPHER_CTX_init(ctx->dctx);
120#else
121 ctx->dctx = EVP_CIPHER_CTX_new();
122#endif
123 EVP_CipherInit_ex(ctx->dctx, NULL, NULL, NULL, (void *)&ivec, -1);
124 EVP_Cipher(ctx->dctx, tmp, C->checksum.data, 24);
125
126 EVP_DigestInit_ex(m, evp_md, NULL);
127 EVP_DigestUpdate(m, tmp, 8); /* confounder */
128 EVP_DigestUpdate(m, data, len);
129 EVP_DigestFinal_ex (m, res, NULL);
130 EVP_MD_CTX_destroy(m);
131 if(ct_memcmp(res, tmp + 8, sizeof(res)) != 0) {
132 krb5_clear_error_message (context);
133 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BAD_INTEGRITY;
134 }
135 memset(tmp, 0, sizeof(tmp));
136 memset(res, 0, sizeof(res));
137 return ret;
138}
139
140#endif

142static krb5_error_code
143RSA_MD5_checksum(krb5_context context,
144 struct _krb5_key_data *key,
145 const void *data,
146 size_t len,
147 unsigned usage,
148 Checksum *C)
149{
150 if (EVP_Digest(data, len, C->checksum.data, NULL, EVP_md5(), NULL) != 1)
151 krb5_abortx(context, "md5 checksum failed");
152 return 0;
153}
154
155struct _krb5_checksum_type _krb5_checksum_rsa_md5 = {
156 CKSUMTYPE_RSA_MD5,
157 "rsa-md5",
158 64,
159 16,
160 F_CPROOF,
161 RSA_MD5_checksum,
162 NULL
163};
